A part of homework 3 that I found very valuable and educational was the first problem, which walked us through deriving the governing equation for a rod temperature profile. Starting with an energy balance and ending with a very simple and clean equation made me really think about and understand the equation and where it comes from. Derivations in general I find to be very useful to learning as you have to look at the equation in more depth as opposed to application problems, though application problems are also useful.  


